OPEN SEASON SPOTLIGHT ü™ê The GLAM Awards (18+)
Sat 19 August 2023

The GLAM Awards are taking over The Tivoli in celebration of all things queer as part of Open Season!

Welcome to The GLAM Awards, an inaugural event that celebrates and honors the achievements of drag queens and queer performers in the entertainment industry in Brisbane and surrounding areas. Presented by DJ Harry K & The Tivoli, this event brings together drag queens, performers, artists, and supporters of the LGBTQI+ community to celebrate the art and culture of drag & queer arts.

Expect a sparkly mix of stunning red-carpet arrivals, iconic main stage performances, and a night to honor the contributions of Drag Queens & Queer Artists that bring so much joy and support to our community. üíñ

üé´ Tickets are on sale now ‚Üí ticketmaster.com.au/event/13005E7C3715A34A

OPEN SEASON SPOTLIGHT ü™ê The Pharcyde with Masta Ace & Marco Polo (18+)
Sun 11 June 2023

Legendary hip-hop collective The Pharcyde will reunite in a rare ‚Äòclass of ‚Äò93‚Äô hip hop collaboration as part of Open Season!

Emerging from the depths of South Central Los Angeles in the late 1980s, the group quickly made their mark by shattering boundaries with their gold-selling debut album, 'Bizarre Ride II The Pharcyde'. Solidifying their place in hip-hop history, they released two more albums before fracturing into two members in the early 2000s.

Now the trio is back, reuniting for a once-in-a-lifetime show at The Tivoli along with hip-hop legends Masta Ace & Marco Polo.

Thu 19 Oct 2023
English legends Happy Mondays are returning to Australia this October as part of their Twenty Four Hour Party People ‚Äì Greatest Hits Tour.
Formed in Salford England, Happy Mondays were one of the most influential groups of the 80s and 90s. Let by frontman Shaun Ryder, the group fused UK‚Äôs indie and emerging Acid house scene to help mint the genre-defying sound that would be become ‚ÄòMadchester‚Äô creating a unique sound that has stood the test of time.
